  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, combine water, fish sauce, soy sauce, rice vinegar, granulated sugar, black pepper, and salt; bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, steam the napa cabbage until tender, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "Split the bao buns in half and toast until lightly browned.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together pork belly and chopped scallions.",
    "Assemble the bao by spreading a tablespoon of the pork belly mixture onto a toasted bun, followed by a portion of steamed cabbage, and drizzling with the simmering liquid.",
    "Repeat for the remaining buns."
